<br>
Like Brad said I was running this raid myself everything from strategy down to organizing all the groups, and funding the peridots.  And it was my first dragon raid.  If you saw my tell counter after I started announcing groups you would know why I couldnt spend to much talking to everyone who wanted join from a 39 druid to 49 bard.  If you sent me another tell I missed sorry you probably arn't the only one.  I did my best to politely tell folks they were too low and sounds like in this case wasn't quite good enough.<br>
<br>
Quite frankly at the time i started announcing the groups the raid was pretty much set and I had done all my recruiting early which I found worked quite well.  As I learned I needed more casters so thats what I will shoot for for next time.<br>
<br>
Hey Kre though I know many people I also did alot of recruiting of folks I barely or had invited before to other events.  My advice to you is just get on your tell machine and set up a raid sometime to kael is an easy place and good starter and invite alot of people.  Have a good fun raid and people remember you.  Do this a few more times and people will truly know you and actively seek you  out to see what your doing in the future.  Between this and guild events I am always busy if I put my time into it.<br>
